# Cleanup

Use this rule before finishing implementation, review, commit, or PR preparation.

> Toggle: `alwaysApply: true` for reliable finish-line cleanup. Set `false` per repo to make it lighter.

## Check For Leftovers

Inspect touched files for accidental leftovers:

- `TODO`, `FIXME`, `HACK`, `XXX`, `TEMP`, `WIP`, and placeholder text.
- `console.log`, `debugger`, temporary traces, mock data, and commented-out code.
- Disabled tests, skipped assertions, temporary feature flags, and broad catch-all fallbacks.
- Notes that say something will be handled later without an issue, owner, or explicit user agreement.

## Decide What To Do

- Remove accidental leftovers before finishing.
- Keep intentional TODOs only when they are clear, scoped, and useful to future work.
- Prefer a tracking issue, ticket ID, or concrete follow-up note for TODOs that remain.
- Do not hide unresolved leftovers. Mention them in the final response or PR notes with the reason they remain.

## Review Stance

When reviewing code, flag leftover markers only when they create real delivery risk, hide incomplete behavior, weaken tests, or make the change harder to maintain.
